Recent push addresses all comments from @maflcko and @stickies-v. Thanks!





> does it make sense to swap it out with `uint256::FromHex`

@kevkevinpal It seems to be used in various tests as well, so it might be worth keeping for the time being.



> Do we expect (present or future) any unordered_ containers keyed by GenTxid?

@cedwies Not that I know of, but if at some point we introduce a `GenTxid` unordered map, then yeah a hasher for GenTxids could make sense. I'm not too sure about the DoS attack potential if it only hashed by txhash and didn't include type? But either way, I think we implement this if needed later on.

